  <li><strong>Producer:</strong> <a href="https://aillio.com" target="_blank">Aillio Limited</a>, Taiwan</li>
  <li><strong>Machine:</strong> Bullet R1</li>
  <li><strong>Connection:</strong> vendor specific USB protocol</li>
  <li><strong>Features:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>logging of drum temperature (DT), bean temperature (BT), exhaust temperature, BT rate-of-rise curves, and voltage</li>
      <li>control of fan, heater and drum speed</li>
      <li>support for the new <a href="https://medium.com/@aillio/the-start-of-something-39aa01d08fa9" target="_blank">IBTS IR sensor</a> and newer models version 1.5 and 2, and firmware versions, has been added in Artisan v1.6.1</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Watch out!</strong> 
To connect successfully, Artisan running on Windows requires the <strong><a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/aillio/bulletr1interface/installation/LibUSB/libusb-win32-bin-1.2.6.0.exe" target="_blank">Aillio USB Drivers For Legacy Version Only</a></strong> <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libusb-win32-bin-1.2.6.0.exe</code>, to be installed.  Link is from <a href="https://legacy.sweetmarias.com/library/aillio-bullet-r1-support/" target="_blank">Sweet Mariaâ€™s legacy support page</a>. For those with V2 there is a workaround for <a href="https://www.home-barista.com/home-roasting/artisan-2-0-and-aillio-bullet-r1-v2-t64271.html#p708297" target="_blank">using Artisan on Windows only</a></p>

<p>Alternatively you can install the legacy serial driver as follows with the Bullet R1 V2 plugged into the USB port of your computer:</p>

<ul class="notice--primary">
  <li>Download and run <a href="https://zadig.akeo.ie/">zadig</a></li>
  <li>You should see the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Aillio LTD - Bullet R 1 ROASTER FS</code> selected</li>
  <li>On the left side you will see your current driver</li>
  <li>On the right side pick <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libusb-win32 (v1.2.6.0)</code></li>
  <li>Install the driver</li>
</ul>

<p class="notice--primary"><strong>Watch out!</strong> For best performance, please start monitoring the
roaster before pre-heating.  Artisan doesnâ€™t monitor unsafe
temperatures, so you should never leave the roaster alone.</p>

<p class="notice--primary"><strong>Watch out!</strong> Running Artisan in parallel with another roast logging software, like RoastTime, connected to the same machine might lead to unstabilities and crashes.</p>
